b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Shogun vs. Sonnen</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 26</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held on August 17, 2013, at the <a href="/wiki/TD_Garden" title="TD Garden">TD Garden</a> in <a href="/wiki/Boston" title="Boston">Boston</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FS1_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-FS1-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was the first <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">UFC</a> event broadcast on <a href="/wiki/Fox_Sports_1" title="Fox Sports 1">Fox Sports 1</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The main event was contested between former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Light_Heavyweight_Champion" title="UFC Light Heavyweight Champion">UFC Light Heavyweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Maur%C3%ADcio_Rua" title="Maur\xc3\xadcio Rua">Maur\xc3\xadcio Rua</a> and <a href="/wiki/Chael_Sonnen" title="Chael Sonnen">Chael Sonnen</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup> The bout was first linked to <a href="/wiki/UFC_161" title="UFC 161">UFC 161</a>, as Sonnen was mentioned as a short notice replacement for Rua\'s original opponent <a href="/wiki/Ant%C3%B4nio_Rog%C3%A9rio_Nogueira" title="Ant\xc3\xb4nio Rog\xc3\xa9rio Nogueira">Ant\xc3\xb4nio Rog\xc3\xa9rio Nogueira</a>, who was out of the bout with a back injury. Visa issues prevented Sonnen from getting into Canada, resulting in Rua being pulled from the event altogether.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Rua/SonnenOff_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-Rua/SonnenOff-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Nick_Ring" title="Nick Ring">Nick Ring</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Uriah_Hall" title="Uriah Hall">Uriah Hall</a> at the event.  However, Ring was pulled from the bout and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Josh_Samman" title="Josh Samman">Josh Samman</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-RingOut/SammanIn_7-0"><a href="#cite_note-RingOut/SammanIn-7">[7]</a></sup> Samman was subsequently forced from the bout and was replaced by returning UFC fighter <a href="/wiki/John_Howard_(fighter)" title="John Howard (fighter)">John Howard</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Akira_Corassani" title="Akira Corassani">Akira Corassani</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Mike_Brown_(fighter)" title="Mike Brown (fighter)">Mike Brown</a> at the event; however, Corassani pulled out of the bout and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Steven_Siler" title="Steven Siler">Steven Siler</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-CorassaniOut/SilerIn_9-0"><a href="#cite_note-CorassaniOut/SilerIn-9">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Thiago_Alves_(fighter)" title="Thiago Alves (fighter)">Thiago Alves</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Matt_Brown_(fighter)" title="Matt Brown (fighter)">Matt Brown</a> at the event; however, Alves pulled out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Mike_Pyle_(fighter)" title="Mike Pyle (fighter)">Mike Pyle</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-AlvesOut/PyleIn_10-0"><a href="#cite_note-AlvesOut/PyleIn-10">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Andy_Ogle" title="Andy Ogle">Andy Ogle</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Conor_McGregor" title="Conor McGregor">Conor McGregor</a> at the event; however, Ogle pulled out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Max_Holloway" title="Max Holloway">Max Holloway</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-OgleOut/HollowayIn_11-0"><a href="#cite_note-OgleOut/HollowayIn-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following is the reported payout to the fighters as reported to the Massachusetts State Athletic Commission. It does not include sponsor money or "locker room" bonuses often given by the UFC and also do not include the UFC\'s traditional "fight night" bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup>\n</p>]'